common.graph

Class AbstractGraph<V extends AbstractVertex<E>,E extends AbstractEdge<V>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • common.CObject
      • common.graph.AbstractGraph<V,E>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of the AbstractVertex
    E - the type of the AbstractEdge
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GraphTemplate

    public abstract class AbstractGraph<V extends AbstractVertex<E>,E extends AbstractEdge<V>>
extends CObject
    The AbstractGraph class is a class representing a graph consisting of: 1) node(s) of type AbstractVertex, and, 2) edge(s) of type AbstractEdge
    Author:
    Vincent Mirian
    Date:
    Nov 15, 2017
